In this letter, President Barack Obama provides a report on the military operations conducted by the United States in support of counterterrorism efforts. The report outlines the deployment of U.S. combat-equipped forces to various locations around the world to enhance the counterterrorism capabilities of allies and disrupt and degrade the capabilities of al-Qa'ida, the Taliban, and associated forces. The report also highlights the ongoing operations in Afghanistan, Somalia, Yemen, Cuba, Niger, Central Africa, Egypt, Kosovo, and other regions. The President emphasizes the commitment to preventing Afghanistan from becoming a safe haven for terrorists and mentions the successful efforts in degrading al-Qa'ida's capabilities and ending the Taliban's leadership in Afghanistan. The letter also mentions the detention operations in Guantanamo Bay, the support provided to regional forces in Africa to address the threat posed by the Lord's Resistance Army, and maritime interception operations to combat terrorist groups. The President concludes by stating that these operations are conducted under his constitutional and statutory authority as Commander in Chief and Chief Executive, and that regular communication with Congress on these deployments will continue.